<TITLE> RMG worker alleges rape </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Savar, Apr 3 (bdnews24.com)  A worker of Savar Textiles at Rajashan in Savar on filed a case on Friday accusing two men of raping her on Wednesday night. A sub-inspector of the Savar Police Station said that the two accused persons  Siddique, the supervisor and Zakir Hossain, a floor-in-charge of the factory  had fled. "We have been trying to detain them." Faruq Kamal, the sub-inspector, and investigation officer of the case, said that the victim had been sent to Dhaka Medical College Hospital for test on Saturday morning. Kamal quoted the complainant saying that Zakir Hossain had tactfully taken the victim to the 3rd floor at 11pm Wednesday. There, Siddique and Zakir raped her. The next day the factory management threatened her not to raise a hue and cry over the matter when the victim complained and demanded action. There was pent up tension among the workers over this matter. Bijoy Kumar Das, manager of the factory refused to talk to the journalists regarding the matter. bdnews24.
